text:
The most common way is to use the Singleton pattern.  In Java, it looks something like this:

class OneOnly {
   public static final OneOnly Singleton = new OneOnly();

   private OneOnly() {
   }
}

To use the OneOnly class, use the OneOnly.Singleton object.  Since the constructor is private, no other classes can make another one.

