text:
Ah, love these kinds of problems.

OK, there is a very efficient solution if you restrict yourself to integer types. Try this code:

int Answer = 0;
int i;
for (i=0; i < 2*n + 1; i++)
{
   Answer ^= Array[i];
}
printf ("Single entry is %d&#92;n", Answer);

The clincher here is that every integer when exclusive ORed with itself yields zero, so all of the duplicates simply disappear - you will only be left with the unpaired entry.

